l table sets the stage for larger parties and gatherings. The furniture is also designed by Brown and similar in spirit to the restaurants cuisine - inspired by the east but adapted for New York. Each piece is handcrafted and sits low to the floor, creating a relaxed eastern aesthetic. Brown effectively lowered the ceiling to make the large, elegant space more intimate by hanging two palas (unique, traditional arched Turkish knives) made of sheetrock and covered with duchess satin.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]", "Gift Cards", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "gift-cards", "", "", "2014-01-27 19:43:04", "2014-01-27 19:43:04", "", "0", "http://pera.gmclients.wpengine.com/?page_id=24", "0", "page", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_2_posts` VALUES("31", "2", "2014-01-27 19:45:15", "2014-01-27 19:45:15", "[vc_row el_class=\"no-padding sub-slider\"][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text][new_royalslider id=\"2\"][/vc_column_text][vc_column_text el_class=\"sub-slider-title\"]\r\n<h1>Concept</h1>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row][vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/1\"][vc_column_text]The latest venture from the Pera team, Pera Soho offers some of the signature meze and entre dishes that made the first Pera so popular, while taking diners palates on a more adventurous journey through the eastern Mediterranean food ways.\r\n\r\nDesigned by DYAMI Architects, Pera Sohos dcor palette blends warm earth tones with splashes of vibrant color and glamorous white accents as seamlessly as it does exotic handcrafted elements with sleekly modern pieces. The overall aesthetic is relaxed refinement that nonetheless evokes a sense of occasion. And indeed an ingenious configuration defines three spaces that are as suitable for private events as they are to a la carte dining, while a large street level private garden and Pera Sohos access to its buildings stunning roof deck presents intriguing al fresco possibilities.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]", "About Us", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "us", "", "", "2014-02-06 15:26:27", "2014-02-06 15:26:27", "", "0", "http://pera.gmclients.wpengine.com/?page_id=31", "0", "page", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_2_posts` VALUES("32", "2", "2014-01-27 19:46:11", "2014-01-27 19:46:11", "[vc_row][vc_column width=\"1/2\" el_class=\"hours-direction\"][vc_text_separator title=\"Hours\" title_align=\"separator_align_center\"][vc_row_inner el_class=\"spacing-bottom\"][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Sunday - Thursday</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>12:00pm - 10:30pm</em></p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">Friday - Saturday</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/2\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>12:00pm - 11:30pm</em></p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><em>*kitchen closes 30 minutes prior to published closing times</em></p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_text_separator title=\"Directions\" title_align=\"separator_align_center\"][vc_column_text el_class=\"no-spacing\"]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\">54 Thompson Street, New York, NY 10012 at the corner of Broome Street</p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Subway</strong></p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"2/3\"][vc_column_text]\r\n<p style=\"text-align: left;\"><span class=\"blue\">E</span> to Spring Street\r\n<span class=\"red\">1</span> to Canal Street\r\n<span class=\"yellow\">N</span> <span class=\"yellow\">Q</span> to Canal Street[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][vc_row_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"1/3\"][vc_column_text]</p>\r\n<p style=\"text-align: center;\"><strong>Parking</strong></p>\r\n[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][vc_column_inner width=\"2/3\"][vc_column_text]<em>Closest garage is on West Broadway between Broome and Grand Streets (1 block away). Other nearby garages are located on West Broadway between Grand and Canal Streets (2 blocks) and on the corner of Grand Street and Wooster Street (2.5 blocks).</em>\r\n\r\n<em>Street parking may be hard to come by in Soho (especially on weekends), the best bets would be on Grand Street, on 6th Avenue and on West Broadway</em>[/vc_column_text][/vc_column_inner][/vc_row_inner][/vc_column][vc_column width=\"1/2\" el_class=\"hours-img\"][vc_gmaps type=\"m\" zoom=\"14\" link=\"https://www.google.com/maps/embed?pb=!1m14!1m8!1m3!1d3023.7339412256215!2d-74.0034359!3d40.72387314999999!3m2!1i1024!2i768!4f13.1!3m3!1m2!1s0x89c2598c80b90e3d%3A0x8c053fe36e7d8561!2sPera+Soho!5e0!3m2!1sen!2sus!4v1391704080527\" size=\"875\"][/vc_column][/vc_row]", "Hours &amp; Directions", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "hours-directions", "", "", "2014-02-20 16:42:51", "2014-02-20 16:42:51", "", "0", "http://pera.gmclients.wpengine.com/?page_id=32", "0", "page", "", "0");
