le sets the stage for larger parties and gatherings. The furniture is also designed by Brown and similar in spirit to the restaurants cuisine - inspired by the east but adapted for New York. Each piece is handcrafted and sits low to the floor, creating a relaxed eastern aesthetic. Brown effectively lowered the ceiling to make the large, elegant space more intimate by hanging two palas (unique, traditional arched Turkish knives) made of sheetrock and covered with duchess satin.[/vc_column_text][/vc_column][/vc_row]", "About Us", "", "publish", "open", "open", "", "us", "", "", "2014-03-30 15:31:52", "2014-03-30 15:31:52", "", "0", "http://pera.gmclients.wpengine.com/?page_id=31", "0", "page", "", "0");
