INSERT INTO `wp_3_posts` VALUES("384", "2", "2013-06-26 09:27:44", "2013-06-26 09:27:44", "As the weather starts heating up and kids are being let out of school, ideas for daily adventures are becoming even more necessary. Finding a pretty green spot for a picnic can be difficult if you dont know where to look. If you live in the city or are visiting, these are some of the best picnic spots NYC has to offer.\n<h2>Strawberry Fields- Central Park</h2>\nOne of the designated quiet spots in Central Park, Strawberry Fields is a perfect place to go and enjoy a picnic on a summer day. Many people still pay tribute to John Lennon here on a daily basis.\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"230\"]<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Imagine_Agosto_2005.JPG\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Italiano: Memorial di John Lennon, negli Straw...\" alt=\"Italiano: Memorial di John Lennon, negli Straw...\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/32/Imagine_Agosto_2005.JPG/300px-Imagine_Agosto_2005.JPG\" width=\"230\" height=\"172\" /></a> John Lennon Memorial in Central Park[/caption]\n\nLocated between 71<sup>st</sup> and 74<sup>th</sup> Streets, this part of Central Parkwas a favorite of Lennon and Yoko Ono. Be sure to see the iconic<i>Imagine</i> mosaic art piece. This is an endorsed Garden of Peace and you will surely find peace of mind spending a little time here.\n<h2>Irish Hunger Memorial- Battery Park</h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"240\"]<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/40092103@N00/2495569094\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"NYC Irish Famine Memorial\" alt=\"NYC Irish Famine Memorial\" src=\"http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3038/2495569094_a6eb3b9a0a_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"180\" /></a> NYC Irish Famine Memorial[/caption]\n\nSnag a bench near this gorgeous memorial dedicated to awareness of the Irish Hunger Famine in the 1800s. It is a unique area with soil,stones, and vegetation all brought from the west coast of Ireland. The cottage ruins are a great place to wander around and appreciate authentic architecture before having a snack and some refreshing drinks. While seemingly an ironic place to have a picnic, its worth the trip for the unique setting and amazing public artwork you get to enjoy.\n<h2>West Side Highway Bike Path</h2>\nThe path offers space for bikers to enjoy nature. You can park yourself anywhere along it and have a great view of the Hudson River while enjoying grass and trees and getting a little fresh air. Particularly beautiful at sunset, consider a dinner picnic and afterward, take a longwalk along the water. Stay out of the way of the bikers though; theyre serious about their space! You can start at Battery Park as a reference point.\n<h2>Washington Market Park- 310 Greenwich St.</h2>\nThis small, kid friendly park offers a bit of shade and green in a nice neighborhood. This park is a simple choice for a picnic in the city, especially if youre already in the Tribeca area. Dont forget to run through the sprinklers when it gets too warm! Alsofree WiFi. You cant beat that!\n<h2>Shakespeare Garden- Central Park</h2>\nAn addition to Central Park in 1916, the Shakespeare Garden has plants and flowers that are mentioned in Shakespeares famous plays.\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"230\"]<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/98153629@N00/4720289276\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Shakespeare Garden in Golden Gate Park\" alt=\"Shakespeare Garden in Golden Gate Park\" src=\"http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4034/4720289276_eb8f88e9a6_m.jpg\" width=\"230\" /></a> Entrance to Shakespeare Garden in Golden Gate Park[/caption]\n\nWhat better place to lay on a blanket or sit on a bench reading Romeo and Juliet while snacking on dried fruits, nuts, cheeses, and meats as they would have during the feast. This beautiful section of Central Park is sure to put you in a romantic state of mind.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<em>Getting outside and enjoying the greenery that New York City has to offer is a great way to connect to nature in an otherwise urban environment. Spend time picni</em><em>cking with friends and family outdoors and get away from the general chaos of the city.</em>\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/?px\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none;float: right\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=8ea180ef-75e9-4bbb-a992-bae50eee1c1d\" /></a></div>", "The Best Picnic Spots in New York City", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "the-best-picnic-spots-in-new-york-city", "", "", "2013-06-26 09:27:44", "2013-06-26 09:27:44", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=384", "0", "post", "", "0");
