INSERT INTO `wp_3_posts` VALUES("458", "2", "2013-06-04 20:28:57", "0000-00-00 00:00:00", "<p dir=\"ltr\">Office holiday parties can sometimes be tedious or awkward events. Spouses finally meeting those people their significant other keeps talking about, making small talk, and the possibility of over indulging are all reasons some people avoid holiday parties- but it doesnt have to be that way!</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Celebrating a holiday is a great opportunity for a group of people who spend most of their waking hours together to relax, unwind, and just have some fun. The 4th of July is a great time to have</p>\n<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/81569586@N00/8043782\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured alignright\" title=\"Volleyball in the Park.\" alt=\"Volleyball in the Park.\" src=\"http://farm1.static.flickr.com/5/8043782_66ed98117f.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"160\" /></a>a picnic or a BBQ and invite family members. Play a game of volleyball or pair people up that dont know each other well to participate in a scavenger hunt. Those that want a little action can participate and those that would rather sit in the shade sipping lemonade can watch, and help judge, the festivities.\n\nMix up your food selections for an interesting twist to your party. If your employees are adventurous types, try something new at the buffet table. Instead of boring hot dogs and hamburgers, have a nacho bar with different\n\n<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Buffet_Portugal.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured alignleft\" title=\"A part of the aniversary buffet\" alt=\"A part of the aniversary buffet\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/58/Buffet_Portugal.jpg/300px-Buffet_Portugal.jpg\" width=\"207\" height=\"155\" /></a>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">salsas and toppings; or arrange to have a local restaurant bring a sampling of their best dishes. Parties are a great time to try something new. No one will forget the new cuisine they got to try or the fun they had a successful office party.</p>\nIf you are holding a party around the Easter holiday, you cant go wrong with an Easter egg hunt for the little ones. To keep the parents entertained as well, try holding an adult Easter egg hunt where the eggs contain candy and cash! Other ideas for egg stuffers are gift cards, additional vacation days, or favors to be done by other coworkers. Who wouldnt want the CEO to have to bring them a cupcake every Friday for a month?\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Halloween is another time to encourage your coworkers to let out their inner child and dress up! Set up a haunted house or hold a costume contest to keep people engaged and entertained. Try categories like Best Coworker Costume, Most Unique, and Most Predictable. Let your coworkers vote and see how well they know each other! Keep it in good fun and encourage positive parodies of one another. Be sure to have prizes and incentives for those that participate in the contests and take lots of pictures! Send them out the following Monday or post on a company bulletin board as an icebreaker or comic relief during a stressful day.</p>\n<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/8810239@N05/3138866918\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured alignleft\" title=\"Christmas cookies\" alt=\"Christmas cookies\" src=\"http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3216/3138866918_e2e5272e96_m.jpg\" width=\"216\" height=\"162\" /></a>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Why not throw a party at an unexpected holiday? If your company has green tendencies,have a party on Arbor Day. Plant a tree with your coworkers and then have a party afterward at a nearby restaurant. You could hold a cheesy Valentines Day party and encourage valentine exchanges or celebrate National Chocolate Chip Cookie day and have everyone bring in a sample of their favorite recipe. Getting creative with what holiday you celebrate may be all you need to add excitement to your parties!</p>\n&nbsp;\n\n<b id=\"docs-internal-guid-7eaef3f0-0bcf-2005-a863-5f29202f63f7\"><a href=\"http://www.peraeventscatering.com/\">Pera Events &amp; Catering</a> can help make your holiday party special with catering or in-house services. Give them a call today!</b>\n\n&nbsp;\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/?px\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none;float: right\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=6826b4e5-ee7b-45ce-a3d7-3606b4cb89c5\" /></a></div>", "How to Add Excitement to Your Office Holiday Party", "", "draft", "closed", "closed", "", "how-to-add-excitement-to-your-company-holiday-party", "", "", "2013-06-04 20:28:57", "0000-00-00 00:00:00", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=458", "0", "post", "", "0");
