INSERT INTO `wp_3_posts` VALUES("848", "2", "2013-06-24 09:25:40", "2013-06-24 09:25:40", "Bland appetizers and safe food choices are out and exotic flavors are in! If for nothing else, people come to business events for the food. Dont disappoint!\n\nAmericans are a diverse group, our heritages rooted all over the world. Greek, Italian, Hispanic, Mediterraneanyou name the culture and youll find examples of the food, albeit maybe an American version, readily available right around the corner. Take advantage of the cuisine available and include tastes of your favorite regions in the food at your next business event.\n\nHaving a common ingredient among a few dishes, some traditional while others have an exotic flair, will introduce your attendees to options they may not have normally considered. Olives are versatile and can be made in many dishes that are both familiar and exotic. Olive tapenade is a classic spread for crackers and bread but black olive hummus adds a Mediterranean twist that will delight party goers. Even adding figs and swapping out cream cheese for goat cheese makes a traditional tapenade fresh and intriguing.\n\nUsing familiar techniques but exotic ingredients allows for clever tastes and accessible culture. Try stuffing phyllo\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"240\"]<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/52042499@N00/5983112789\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"The Spread\" alt=\"The Spread\" src=\"http://farm7.static.flickr.com/6012/5983112789_5d99266cbf_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"180\" /></a> Get creative with your food options[/caption]\n\na dough with feta, spinach, and olives to add a Greek twist to handheld snacks. Serve up dill and lemon seasoned Greek yogurt dip alongside Ranch for dipping vegetables. Mini caprese appetizers are not only popular but give a nod to classic Italian flavors in an easy-to-handle package. Spear a cherry tomato, mozzarella, and fresh basil with a toothpick and drizzle the whole plate with balsamic.\n\nHaving a buffet spread or a snack table is a popular way to have appetizers at an event. Keeping one place stocked takes the hassle out of multiple stations or having a wait staff. Chips and salsa is popular at events, but featuring salsa is a great way to make the familiar, exotic. Salsa verde, fresh pico de gallo, spicy smoked chipotle salsa, and queso can all be offered to make a now-boring standard into an interesting spread. Just be sure to label those flavors that are hotter than others- many people arent used to spicy foods!\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"200\"]<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Kisir.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"English: &quot;Ksr&quot; is a couscous salad...\" alt=\"English: &quot;Ksr&quot; is a couscous salad...\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/e6/Kisir.jpg/300px-Kisir.jpg\" width=\"200\" /></a> \"Kisir\" is a Turkish couscous salad.[/caption]\n\nHaving an exotic salad selection makes a traditional, sometimes boring, dish into something inspiring. Couscous based salads with fresh vegetables and light sauces are healthy and, while they are traditional Mediterranean dishes, they are exotic here in the US. Fresh mint and basil keep these salads light and fresh. Including this type of salad as alternative or accompaniment to pasta salad or coleslaw makes a hamburger or sandwich more interesting.\n\nThere is no longer a need to have boring food at any event. With fresh ingredients and ideas readily available, any company can offer exotic flavors and remain in budget and keep with their company ideals. You can be as creative or as traditional as youd like but incorporating special dishes will surprise and interest your attendees. Break out of the typical mold and offer something your customers will be talking about at the next party!\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"></div>", "How to Have the Perfect Mix of Exotic and Familiar Foods at Your Business Event", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "how-to-have-the-perfect-mix-of-exotic-and-familiar-foods-at-your-business-event", "", "", "2013-06-24 09:25:40", "2013-06-24 09:25:40", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=848", "0", "post", "", "0");
