INSERT INTO `wp_3_posts` VALUES("1026", "2", "2013-09-19 13:36:35", "2013-09-19 13:36:35", "Turkish cuisine is characterized by its colorful, flavorful and aromatic spices. Among some of its most widely-used spices are paprika, cumin, oregano, allspice and cinnamon. The combination of these and other spices gives Turkish dishes a distinct flavor, transforming meats and accentuating mezes.\n<h2>Paprika</h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"100\"]<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Spanishsmokedpaprika.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"A small bowl of hot smoked Spanish paprika (pi...\" alt=\"A small bowl of hot smoked Spanish paprika (pi...\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/97/Spanishsmokedpaprika.jpg/75px-Spanishsmokedpaprika.jpg\" width=\"100\" /></a> Hot smoked paprika.[/caption]\n\nIn Turkish cooking, paprika is used for its sweet flavor, smokey aroma and vivid red color. Rather than using paprika for hotness and spice like in Hungarian and Cajun cuisine, it is typically used to season meat dishes like lamb kebabs in order to give them mild flavor and a dose of bright red color. It is also used as a garnish in vegetarian dishes like red lentil soup and Turkish omelets called menemen.\n<h2>Cumin</h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"100\"]<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Dry-cumin-seeds.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Dry cumin seeds\" alt=\"Dry cumin seeds\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/62/Dry-cumin-seeds.jpg/75px-Dry-cumin-seeds.jpg\" width=\"100\" /></a> Dry cumin seeds[/caption]\n\nCumin is most commonly used in wrapped dishes, or dolmas, to lend a rich, zesty flavor with earthy undertones. These wrapped dishes usually contain vegetables like cabbage, spinach and grape leaves. Cumin is also used in unwrapped meat dishes in combination with other Turkish spices.\n<h2>Oregano</h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"100\"]<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Oregano_dried_.JPG\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"English: oregano\" alt=\"English: oregano\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/90/Oregano_dried_.JPG/75px-Oregano_dried_.JPG\" width=\"100\" /></a> Oregano[/caption]\n\nOregano is a common herb in many kinds of cuisines around the world, though it has a prominent place in Turkish cooking. Freshly picked oregano has a slightly tart flavor and is used as a seasoning for coban salatasi, otherwise known as shepherd\'s salad, or dried and sprinkled as a garnish on top of grilled lamb and beef dishes.\n<h2>Allspice</h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"100\"]<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:AllspiceBowl.JPG\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"English: Whole allspice berries in a bowl\" alt=\"English: Whole allspice berries in a bowl\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/d1/AllspiceBowl.JPG/75px-AllspiceBowl.JPG\" width=\"100\" /></a> Whole allspice berries[/caption]\n\nAllspice is a peppery, savory spice made from the dried berries of the pimento plant that are similar in appearance to peppercorns. It is used as a rub in lamb and beef dishes prior to cooking as well as wrapped dishes like stuffed cabbage and grape leaves. Many simple vegetable dolmas are prepared using seasonings like allspice, garlic and salt.\n<h2>Cinnamon</h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"100\"]<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Canelle_Cinnamomum_verum_Luc_Viatour_crop1.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"English: cinnamon bark Cinnamomum verum. Fran...\" alt=\"English: cinnamon bark Cinnamomum verum. Fran...\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/d/da/Canelle_Cinnamomum_verum_Luc_Viatour_crop1.jpg/300px-Canelle_Cinnamomum_verum_Luc_Viatour_crop1.jpg\" width=\"100\" /></a> Cinnamon bark[/caption]\n\nAside from honey, cinnamon is the most common ingredient in Turkish dessert dishes. It is featured prominently in a rice pudding called zerde, where it is used for its sweet and spicy taste. Cezerye is a dessert made with caramelized carrots, cinnamon and nuts, which is then cooled to form thin, crunchy squares.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nMany of the recipes that use these spices have been passed down from generation to generation and are still prepared in Turkey today. These spices are also widely available in grocery stores around the world, which makes it easy to purchase them for your own homemade recipes.\n\n&nbsp;\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"></div>", "Key Turkish Spices", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "key-turkish-spices", "", "", "2013-09-19 13:36:35", "2013-09-19 13:36:35", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=1026", "0", "post", "", "0");
