INSERT INTO `wp_3_posts` VALUES("1204", "2", "2013-11-14 19:13:27", "2013-11-14 19:13:27", "Ayran is defined as a cold, salty, yogurt beverage and is native to Turkey, Afghanistan, Lebanon, the Balkans, and can even be found in North Caucasus. Though this unique drink can be found in places other Turkey, only in Turkey is it the national beverage (as opposed to the national drink, which is considered to be Raki).\n\nAyran, or Turkish buttermilk as it is sometimes called, dates back thousands of years to the ancient Gokturks who would dilute the bitter yogurt drink with water in an attempt to improve the taste. Eventually, it became the popular yogurt drink associated with Turkey.\n\nWhile many Turkish citizens either love the salty yogurt drink, Westerners are also falling in love with the drink, albeit not always at first sight. There are many reasons for the drink\'s rise in popularity, and one of the top reasons is the health benefits associated with ayran. This sugar free drink not only brings all the health benefits associated with yogurt consumption, but it also can help the body to retain salt. An important benefit on especially hot days when the body is in danger of losing too much salt.\n\nThe drink\'s rise in popularity has grown so much that now kits and instructional videos are available to make your own ayran. It is now possible to relive your unique Turkish experience in your own home. This uniquely Turkish drink manages to stir up strong emotions, but no matter anyone\'s personal feelings, ayran will always be a part of Turkish culture and heritage.\n\n&nbsp;\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/?px\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none;float: right\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=18a48c3e-4609-4b3d-95c8-66b86be3a7f0\" /></a></div>", "Ayran-Unique Drink Experience of Turkey", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "ayran-unique-drink-experience-of-turkey", "", "", "2013-11-14 19:13:27", "2013-11-14 19:13:27", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=1204", "0", "post", "", "0");
