INSERT INTO `wp_3_posts` VALUES("1294", "2", "2013-02-28 09:00:15", "2013-02-28 09:00:15", "When people think about weddings they often remember what they had to eat during the meal.\n\nYour wedding is one of the biggest days in your life. Its a day you spend with family and friends. Theyre all excited about the ceremony. They want to celebrate your love and happiness.\n\nTheyre also looking forward to having a great meal.\n\nWe want to make sure your big day goes off just as you hope. To make sure everyone has a meal to remember weve put together everything you need to know about wedding reception catering.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"150\"]<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Whitweddingcake.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"A contemporary white wedding cake decorated wi...\" alt=\"A contemporary white wedding cake decorated wi...\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/4/47/Whitweddingcake.jpg/300px-Whitweddingcake.jpg\" width=\"150\" /></a> Add a simple twist to your menu items to make them memorable. (Photo credit: Wikipedia)[/caption]\n\n<b>Memorable Menu Items</b>\n\nYou want to have a wedding menu with memorable items. Your guests have been to weddings before and theyve likely had similar meals at each.\n\nHaving unique items on the menu will have them excited when they sit down for the meal. Theyll be talking about what they had for days. Theres even a good chance that when they think of your wedding theyll remember the delicious dinner.\n\nInstead of going with the usual Chefs Salad or Caesar Salad, go with Mediterranean Pheasant Salad or Watermelon and Feta Salad. Both take the regular salad to new levels of flavor that will leave your guests with smiles on their faces.\n\nA simple twist with an ingredient like pheasant or watermelon will take the first course on your wedding menu from regular to memorable.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"160\"]<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/21439826@N00/780456429\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Wedding Dinner Table\" alt=\"Wedding Dinner Table\" src=\"http://farm2.static.flickr.com/1001/780456429_4a0778534a_m.jpg\" width=\"160\" height=\"240\" /></a> Don\'t forget important details like table dressings &amp; dining ware. (Photo credit: chrisheuer)[/caption]\n\n<b>Complete Menu and Equipment Packages</b>\n\nSomething that can surprise couples when it comes to planning their wedding is figuring out whats included with each of the packages they reserve.\n\nSometimes the host location will provide much of whats necessary for a great reception. Other times, its the job of the caterer to provide more than just the food.\n\nOnce you have your location chosen, approach the caterer and ask for everything you need to complete the plans.\n\nThe right caterer will fill out everything you need to complete the reception including seating, tables, table dressings, dining wares, serving staff and the meals.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>One Main Contact Person</b>\n\nIts good to have one person that acts as the main owner of your wedding reception meal. Your caterer will work with you in the months leading up to the big day as you work through the details of the menu together.\n\nYour contact will introduce you to items by allowing you to have a tasting. They will plan out how the meal will be served including the serving schedule.\n\nYour contact will work with you through the entire process and will be available on the day itself. They will be there on site so they can make sure the meal goes off without incident leaving you to focus only on enjoying your big day.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>Speak With Past Clients</b>\n\nThe best caterer will let you speak with their past clients.\n\nBy speaking with former clients youll learn about how things went for their wedding.\n\nNewlyweds dont have experience planning weddings in many cases. Its good to hear from others that have gone through it before. You can listen to their experiences and make adjustments to your preparations.\n\nThe caterer will help you prepare for everything. Speaking with past clients and hearing their success stories will give you peace of mind because youll be hearing from someone that was in your position.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b>Conclusion</b>\n\nThe time leading up to your wedding can be stressful.\n\nHaving a memorable menu for your dinner is something that can leave a lasting impact for you and your guests.\n\nFollow the items above as you prepare to have your wedding catered. If you do, youll be in a great position to have a great wedding dinner that will leave your guests talking about your reception for years.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<i>To have a memorable wedding of your own please </i><a href=\"http://www.peraeventscatering.com/contact_us.html\"><i>contact Pera</i></a><i> today for complete catering details.</i>\n\n&nbsp;\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/?px\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none;float: right\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=5a9a4b79-6306-4c55-9737-cefd7956d09c\" /></a></div>", "Everything You Need to Know About Wedding Reception Catering", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "everything-you-need-to-know-about-wedding-reception-catering", "", "", "2013-02-28 09:00:15", "2013-02-28 09:00:15", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=80", "0", "post", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_3_posts` VALUES("1295", "2", "2013-03-11 09:00:35", "2013-03-11 09:00:35", "The rehearsal dinner before your wedding is, in a way, your first event as husband and wife.\n\nDepending on the size of dinner you want, mutual friends, family from both sides, and family friends all come together to join you in celebrating your future.\nWhile there are many things to consider when planning your rehearsal dinner, the most important things besides the food itself are:\n Guest list\n Location\n Activities\n\nYour rehearsal dinner should reflect your style as a couple, while showing thoughtful consideration to your guests.\n<h1>The Guest List</h1>\nThere are no rules when creating the invite list to your rehearsal dinner. It can be a quiet dinner for the two of you and your immediate families or it can include everyone you plan on having at the wedding. Depending on your desires and budgets, you can find a restaurant or a caterer to meet your needs.\nAs with the rest of your wedding, its your event. Cater to your style and tastes and you cant go wrong!\n\n[caption id=\"attachment_118\" align=\"aligncenter\" width=\"197\"]<a href=\"http://midtown.pera.wpengine.com/wp-content/blogs.dir/3/2013/03/guest-list.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-118 \" alt=\"Tailor your guest list to suit the mood of your wedding.\" src=\"http://midtown.pera.wpengine.com/wp-content/blogs.dir/3/2013/03/guest-list-197x300.jpg\" width=\"197\" height=\"300\" /></a> Tailor your guest list to suit the mood of your wedding.[/caption]\n<h1>The Location</h1>\nThe most important thing when choosing a venue, besides whether or not it can hold the number of people you plan to invite, is if it is easily accessible for all parties involved. You arent going to have a good time if you need a crane to get grandma in her wheelchair onto a river barge where the dinner is being held.\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"240\"]<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/88995969@N00/5907701480\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Mariachis at the Rehearsal Dinner\" alt=\"Mariachis at the Rehearsal Dinner\" src=\"http://farm7.static.flickr.com/6060/5907701480_6507d864c9.jpg\" width=\"240\" /></a> Location, location, location (Photo credit: cariberry)[/caption]\n\nConsider if you want small children at the event and be specific on invitations if the venue isnt appropriate for children. A helpful service available for events like this is onsite babysitting. Having the peace of mind that their children are nearby but not underfoot will help your guests with young children relax and have a good time.\n\n&nbsp;\n\nYour guests are what will make your night memorable.\n\nAs the bride-to-be, think about what your future in-laws might enjoy.\n\nFor example, serve your father-in-laws favorite dessert or if it isnt one of your wedding colors, use your mother-in-laws favorite color for the centerpieces.\nA nod to your future in-laws without allowing their desires to take over the whole event is key.\n<h1>The Activities</h1>\nIf you choose to invite everyone, keep in mind many of the people attending your rehearsal dinner may not have met the majority of the other people that will be at your wedding. When friends and family fly in from across the country, ensure they know they are invited to the dinner and make a point to tell them youd appreciate their attendance. If you choose to have a smaller event, think about holding it two nights before your wedding and reserve the night before for out of town guests. Make time outside of the ceremony to see those that are there for the special day.\n\nCreate icebreakers like games or nametags that will get conversations started. These people are going to be one big happy family linked together by you and your future husband. Its important they get to know each other. Its hard to remain formal and shy when theres a game of horseshoes or volleyball happening nearby.\n\nLuckily, they will always have something to talk about as they are there for you and your fianc!\n<h1>Conclusion</h1>\nLastly, remember that you and your fianc are throwing this event. You are starting a life together and want to show the world youre a united front that made choices together.\n\nSure, your mothers ideal rehearsal dinner may be a six-course dinner with fine linens and candlelight, but if the two of you would prefer an afternoon outdoor buffet with games and dancing with a live band- its your party, hire the band!\nYour mother will have a great time and it will set a precedent for your future family.\n\n<strong>Pera offers complete packages for <a title=\"Pera Events &amp; Catering\" href=\"http://www.peraeventscatering.com/\" target=\"_blank\">private events</a>. Contact us today to discuss your rehearsal dinner or any other event youre planning!</strong>\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/?px\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none;float: right\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=38c90fdb-c1e4-411b-a4d5-76b99752fbbf\" /></a></div>", "Rehearsal Dinner 101: Everything for Your Checklist", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "rehearsal-dinner-101-everything-for-your-checklist", "", "", "2013-03-11 09:00:35", "2013-03-11 09:00:35", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=111", "0", "post", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_3_posts` VALUES("1296", "2", "2013-03-21 15:24:23", "2013-03-21 15:24:23", "There are many things to consider when arranging a corporate event and feeding your employees and clientele is one of the major ones.\n\nThe things to keep in mind when choosing food options are:\n<ul>\n	<li>the size of your crowd</li>\n	<li>the length of time theyll be required or expected to attend your events</li>\n	<li>what your facility is capable of handling in terms of serving and seating</li>\n</ul>\nAs always, consider your budget.\n<h1>The Crowd</h1>\nYou have a list of clients that are attending your event and you know how many employees will be attending. Have you considered people who may bring a spouse or guest if that is acceptable, or whether or not your wait staff and other event staff have meals included in their contracts? Calculate the number of people you think are attending and that you need to feed and add 5-10%. Its better to have too much food that can be donated to a shelter or other organization than run out of food before youve fed everyone at your event.\n\nDepending on how you can distribute food, prominently list what may contain nuts or gluten and note if items have meat in them. The last thing you want at an event is an allergic reaction to the food provided or a vegetarian accidently eating beef broth.\n\nIf you event has a theme or style, consider matching the food for a fun twist. If youre discussing international sales revenue, have lunch tailored to your top selling countrys cuisine. It all depends on your corporate guidelines how much fun you can have with gearing the food to a theme at your event.\n<h1>The Schedule</h1>\nWhat time does your event start? If your event is starting mid-morning and you have time to offer a full breakfast, it will be appreciated by your attendees. Otherwise, coffee and pastries on a table off to the side is nice for those who had to rush to be on time or need a pick-me-up mid-way through the morning.\n\nEven if your event starts a bit later in the morning, people will still be expecting lunch mid-day. Try to schedule events to allow for an hour for lunch in between if you are taking a true break. If you are expecting to work through lunch, be sure to serve something easily eaten without much cutting or holding, like salads or sandwiches. Trying to eat a messy burrito or cut a steak will detract from progress.\n<h1>The Facility</h1>\nAre you packing people in to a lecture hall for the day or do you have the luxury of a dining room next to the ballroom where you event is held? Are you holding a day-long meeting in your in-office conference room or are you arranging catering for your companys yearly corporate gathering? If you have the space for a buffet set up and you have the dining tables and chairs available, this is usually the easiest solution.\n\nBoxed lunches that are available on a table or from an attendant are also good choices if you dont have space for a buffet or the facilities to handle dishes. This also allows event attendees to grab a box and go outside if its a nice day or eat later if they have something to take care of over the lunch hour.", "How to Choose the Best Food Options for Corporate Events", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "how-to-choose-the-best-food-options-for-corporate-events", "", "", "2013-03-21 15:24:23", "2013-03-21 15:24:23", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=124", "0", "post", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_3_posts` VALUES("1297", "2", "2013-04-01 15:58:03", "2013-04-01 15:58:03", "<span>Many occasions call for an in-office lunch to be held.</span>\n\n<span>Perhaps you have important clients coming in and it isnt feasible to get them all to a restaurant and back for lunch.</span>\n\n<span>You might want to treat your employees to lunch while discussing company objectives.</span>\n\n<span>Whatever the case may be, there are a few options to consider when planning an effective in-office business lunch.</span>\n\n- Where do you plan on eating?\n\n- How many people will be attending?\n\n- How classy or casual do you want to go?\n<h2></h2>\n<h2><span><b>The Location  </b></span></h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"200\"]<img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"English: &quot;Wilshire Room,&quot; company in...\" alt=\"English: &quot;Wilshire Room,&quot; company in...\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/4/4f/Conferenceroom2.JPG\" width=\"200\" /> <span>Conference rooms are an easy business lunch venue.</span>[/caption]\n\n<span>If you plan on holding the lunch meeting in a conference room, your seating has been taken care of for you. Try to ensure each person has enough table space or what you serve is easily eaten off a plate balanced in a lap.</span>\n\n<span>Conference rooms are easy. What if you have employees that work on the shop floor and you want to have a lunch meeting in the middle of a day of training? If you have the option of setting up a temporary dining area where your employees can still see their presenter, this will make everything easier for your employees.</span>\n\n<span>If this isnt an option, consider what kind of food you should serve. Sandwiches, chips or fruit, and soft drinks in cans are a good choice. Pizza is also a crowd pleaser that can be easily contained on a plate and eaten with one hand.</span>\n<h2></h2>\n<h2><span><b>Attendance</b></span></h2>\n<span>You know how many employees you have. What about the number of clients if you are planning lunch for a client meeting? Do you know who is coming or do you just know you will be hosting a few people from a certain company?</span>\n\n<span>If you cant get an accurate head count beforehand and you want catering that requires advance ordering, as opposed to simple sandwiches from the deli around the corner, you may have to do some guess work.</span>\n\n<span>If you often hold in-office lunches, you may want to hold onto the takeout menus from restaurants around your office area that can deliver the same day. Show these options to customers when they come in and ask them to place orders before going into their meeting.</span>\n\n<span>If your business relationship allows, ask the person youre arranging the meeting with how many people they think will be attending. Otherwise, order extra and youll have some happy employees that didnt attend the meeting eating leftovers in the kitchen!</span>\n<h2></h2>\n<h2><span><b>Style</b></span></h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"200\"]<img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"The standard Swedish lunch. The crackers on th...\" alt=\"The standard Swedish lunch. The crackers on th...\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/c/c7/School_lunch.jpg/300px-School_lunch.jpg\" width=\"200\" /> <span>Choose a style of food that suits the mood and purpose of your business lunch</span>[/caption]\n\n<span>Certain in-office lunch events may call for first class service and food. Your office may be more casual, where barbeque would be the fare of choice and greatly appreciated by your staff.</span>\n\n<span>Whether you want to serve individual lunches off a catering menu or an assortment of food choices for your attendees to choose from, you will end up with happy, well-fed people if you thoughtfully plan your event.</span>\n\n<span>No matter what you chose to do for your office lunch meeting, <a href=\"http://www.peraeventscatering.com/\"><span>Pera Events Catering</span></a> can help make it memorable and successful.</span>\n\n<span>And of course, dont forget the napkins!</span>\n<h6 class=\"zemanta-related-title\" style=\"font-size: 1em\">Related articles</h6>\n<ul class=\"zemanta-article-ul zemanta-article-ul-image\" style=\"margin: 0;padding: 0;overflow: hidden\">\n	<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li-image zemanta-article-ul-li\" style=\"padding: 0;background: none;float: left;vertical-align: top;text-align: left;width: 84px;font-size: 11px;margin: 2px 10px 10px 2px\"><a style=\"padding: 2px;text-decoration: none\" href=\"http://peranyc.com/blog/how-to-choose-the-best-food-options-for-corporate-events/\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"padding: 0;margin: 0;border: 0;width: 80px\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://i.zemanta.com/154036631_80_80.jpg\" /></a><a style=\"overflow: hidden;text-decoration: none;line-height: 12pt;height: 80px;padding: 5px 2px 0 2px\" href=\"http://peranyc.com/blog/how-to-choose-the-best-food-options-for-corporate-events/\" target=\"_blank\">How to Choose the Best Food Options for Corporate Events</a></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/?px\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none;float: right\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=7d4dd9e4-c6ad-48e4-a345-c0b38add7dd3\" /></a></div>", "How to Plan A Successful In-Office Business Lunch Meeting", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "how-to-plan-a-successful-in-office-business-lunch-meeting", "", "", "2013-04-01 15:58:03", "2013-04-01 15:58:03", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=136", "0", "post", "", "0");
INSERT INTO `wp_3_posts` VALUES("1298", "2", "2013-04-10 16:27:28", "2013-04-10 16:27:28", "A cocktail hour during your wedding events is an excellent time for your two families to mingle and get to know each other.\n\nIt allows you to see all your guests where you may not get much quality time with them when caught up in the whirlwind of your wedding later.\n\nConsiderations for your cocktail hour should include:\n<ul>\n	<li>The time frame within your other wedding events</li>\n	<li>Your chosen venue and its services</li>\n	<li>The menu</li>\n</ul>\n&nbsp;\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Wedding_on_the_Beach_Modern_Art_Photograph.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"English: Trash the dress photograph taken on t...\" alt=\"English: Trash the dress photograph taken on t...\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/3/3a/Wedding_on_the_Beach_Modern_Art_Photograph.jpg/300px-Wedding_on_the_Beach_Modern_Art_Photograph.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"197\" /></a> A sunset cocktail hour will capture the magic of the evening.[/caption]\n<h2><b>Time Frame</b></h2>\nThere are many appropriate times to slip in a cocktail hour.\n\nYou may choose to hold a cocktail hour at the beginning of your wedding festivities when friends and family begin to arrive. This gives you the chance to see and talk to everyone before you are needed for photos or cake cutting or any other bride and groom moment that may occur.\n\nAnother great time for a cocktail hour is right after your ceremony and before your true reception. This is often when wedding photographers like to take still shots. Your wedding attendees can all go gush over your dress and the flowers over a cocktail or beer while you are getting your photos done.\n\nBefore your rehearsal dinner is another time that a cocktail hour would be appropriate and appreciated. This gives your guests a chance to meet each other before sitting down to dinner and allows you to make rounds and see everywhere which may be more difficult later.\n\nIt also allows those of your guests who know themselves to be perpetually late to slip in without being obvious about it!\n\n&nbsp;\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"240\"]<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/21424326@N00/6932116954\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"#cocktail hour\" alt=\"#cocktail hour\" src=\"http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5319/6932116954_9642fe9372_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"240\" /></a> Location, location, location[/caption]\n<h2><b>The Venue</b></h2>\nYou may want to hold your cocktail hour at your favorite local bar if youre getting married near home. The venue you have chosen to hold your wedding may have a cocktail bar that can be reserved before or after your wedding.\n\nWhat other features are offered at the venue?\n\nIs there a place where a babysitter or nanny could watch young children so parents can enjoy a cocktail without worrying about their kids being all the way at home?\n\nIf your wedding is during one of the colder months, see if there is a coat check available so guests wont have to wrestle with a parka while sipping a martini and meeting your extended family.\n\nAny additional services that make your guests more comfortable and add convenience will be well received and appreciated.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><b>Menu</b></h2>\nYou can choose to have a few cocktail options that are carried on trays by waiters or provide an open bar where people can ask for their favorite drink. If you expect that someone may make a toast, champagne is always a good choice to have available.\n\nIts nice to also provide snacks or hors doeuvres during a cocktail hour. Your guests can snack on small things while sipping cocktails and chatting. This creates a friendly atmosphere and, if all other conversation topics fail, they can always talk about the food!\n\n---\n\nYour wedding\'s cocktail hour is a great opportunity to give your guests a chance to eat, drink and talk. With a well-chosen time, venue and menu, it surely will make the whole wedding an even more festive event.\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/?px\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none;float: right\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=1891e1de-ab08-47dc-ac16-2ac94321c0e3\" /></a></div>", "Plan the Perfect Catered Cocktail Hour at Your Wedding", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "plan-the-perfect-catered-cocktail-hour-at-your-wedding", "", "", "2013-04-10 16:27:28", "2013-04-10 16:27:28", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=157", "0", "post", "", "0");
