INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("10", "2", "2013-02-14 15:10:22", "2013-02-14 15:10:22", "Business dinners are important.\n\nAs the host youre looking to give your guests something theyll remember. You want them to be engaged and conversational. This mood helps the business and relationship goals you wish to achieve in helping establish or reward long-term and profitable partnerships.\n\nHosting the dinner at your office or in a location that can understand and specifically cater to your wishes puts you in charge. You can control the menu and make sure the private party is a first class event.\n\nHere are ten unique ideas for your next business dinner.\n\n&nbsp;\n<h1>10 Unique Ideas for Business Dinners</h1>\n<b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"></span></b>\n<h2><b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">Appetizer Course</span></b></h2>\n<b>1. Portuguese Fried Calamari</b>\n\nWhen guests arrive at dinner they are excited. Their senses are starved for something interesting and out of the ordinary. Portuguese-style Calamari is the perfect item to get things started, it is familiar and popular, while at the same time unique. You get the crunch of the spiced batter and the unique texture of the calamari, plus the earthy flavor from the pastirma and spicy kick from pickled peppers.\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"240\"]<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/43351991@N04/4296156428\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Bacon Wrapped Stuffed Dates 4of4\" alt=\"Bacon Wrapped Stuffed Dates 4of4\" src=\"http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4014/4296156428_2b1ce78d30_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"155\" /></a> Stuffed Dates (Photo credit: Food Thinkers)[/caption]\n\n<b>2. Pastirma-Wrapped Feta-Stuffed Dates</b>\n\nDates are a standard delicacy in Mediterranean culture. When wrapped with delicious pastirma they become even more flavorful and fulfilling. Pastirma is a cured beef from Turkey. Its a popular ingredient in Mediterranean cooking.\n\n<b>3. Watermelon &amp; Feta Salad</b>\n\nSalad is the most common appetizer or first course for any dinner. Add variety and flavor to the traditional salad with watermelon and feta cheese. With this salad you get an extra element of surprise sure to leave a lasting impression on your guests.\n\n<b>4. Mediterranean Meatballs</b>\n\nMeatballs make a great starter for a dinner. It gives sustenance to the meal. This preparation is full of unique flavors. The spices and the sauce create a unique blend that drives the senses wild.\n\n<b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"></span></b>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">Main Course</span></b></h2>\n<b>5. Chicken Brochette</b>\n\nChicken is an ingredient used in restaurants of all kinds, but it can be boring. To make the chicken on your business dinner menu satisfying go with the Chicken Brochette. The chicken is tender, moist, lightly spiced and fire-roasted.<b></b>\n\n<b></b><b>6. Lamb Adana</b>\n\nPera\'s signature hand-ground lamb preparation has been a crowd pleaser since day 1 and has turned many guests hesitant to try lamb into lamb lovers (or at least Lamb Adana lovers). We will prepare them pre-rolled in lavash bread with their garnish salads, making it a ready to eat menu item whether as a main course or a filling appetizer.\n\n<b>7. Sliced Sirloin Shaslik Steak</b>\n\nSteak is usually a requirement for a dinner menu. Many of your guests will expect an exquisite steak preparation and you can blow them away with this item. It is sliced and skewered, comes with peppers and onions and a unique bulghar pilaf that has a nutty flavor blended with herbs. Its something your guests will love.\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"240\"]<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/21309047@N00/6041522909\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Roast Salmon, baby baked potatoes, carrots &amp; g...\" alt=\"Roast Salmon, baby baked potatoes, carrots &amp; g...\" src=\"http://farm7.static.flickr.com/6204/6041522909_eedd61427a_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"180\" /></a> Roast Salmon, baby baked potatoes, carrots &amp; green beans (Photo credit: Annie Mole)[/caption]\n\n<b>8. Pan-Roasted Salmon</b>\n\nIs it inevitable to feature salmon? Not at all. But why swim against the current when you can have such a familiar dish cooked to perfection and accompanied by garnishes to bring one of a kind tastes out of the salmon whether it be a chopped fresh vegetable salad or a whipped dill and yoghurt dressing with sea salt crystals.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\"></span></b>\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2><b><span style=\"text-decoration: underline\">Dessert Course</span></b></h2>\n<b>9. Seasonal Fresh Fruits</b>\n\nFruit gives your guests a healthy alternative to the traditional dessert. Make the item memorable by going with seasonal fresh fruit paired with fresh mint and an aromatic rose petal syrup.\n\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Chocolate_Torte_at_Nino%27s_Tuscany_in_NYC%2C_March_2010.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Chocolate Torte at Nino\'s Tuscany in New York ...\" alt=\"Chocolate Torte at Nino\'s Tuscany in New York ...\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/84/Chocolate_Torte_at_Nino%27s_Tuscany_in_NYC%2C_March_2010.jpg/300px-Chocolate_Torte_at_Nino%27s_Tuscany_in_NYC%2C_March_2010.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a> Chocolate Torte. (Photo credit: Wikipedia)[/caption]\n\n<b>10. Dark Chocolate Hazelnut Torte</b>\n\nFor guests that need to give in to their sweet tooth you can offer this item. Chocolate lovers will be amazed by the rich flavor and sweet taste of the apricot marmalade. Nut-free preparation also possible with advance notice.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n<b></b>\n\n<b>Always Leave Them Wanting More</b>\n\nBusiness dinners can be stressful. The right menu items will make all the difference.\n\nGo with the upscale ideas above and youll leave guests talking about the wonderful dinner they had for days. That means a lasting impression of you and your company.\n\nYour guests will be smiling and so will you.\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n\n&nbsp;\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/?px\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none;float: right\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=e4f36824-ae97-45e4-89d5-8c94ce623407\" /></a></div>", "10 Unique Ideas for Business Dinners", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "10-unique-ideas-for-business-dinners", "", "", "2013-02-14 15:10:22", "2013-02-14 15:10:22", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=10", "0", "post", "", "0");
