INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("164", "2", "2013-05-10 16:02:23", "2013-05-10 16:02:23", "Are you ready to throw an office party?\n\nHolidays, product launches and grand openings are a few types of parties and events. Companies hostevents to allow employees to enjoy time together outside of the typical work setting. These eventsimprove corporate culture and elevate productivity and employee satisfaction.\n\nThe challenge for a company that hosts and event is how to organize. Sometimes events are simpleparties held in the office and other times the parties are more extravagant events at offsite locations. Inboth situations the event needs catering that includes food and drink.\n\nIf you have an office event coming up here are some tips on how to plan the catering.\n<h1><b>In-Office Events</b></h1>\nIn-office events can include holiday parties for employees and their families. An even could also be thelaunching of a new product where you have employees and clients in attendance. Make sure there isroom for people to congregate as they eat and as they converse. Also designate an area for the buffettable where the caterer can lay out the menu items. Have a separate area for the drink table or bar soyou dont end up with a bottleneck or people only congregating in one area. People tend to stick nearthe food or the bar!\n\nAsk your caterer for popular food items. <a title=\"How to choose the best food options for corporate events\" href=\"http://peranyc.com/blog/how-to-choose-the-best-food-options-for-corporate-events/\" target=\"_blank\">Quality caterers can take your ideas for the food and createmeals that will be easy and delicious</a>. You can work together to come up with a menu that satisfieseveryone that will attend.\n\nA few final considerations for in-office events include adding snack items outside of the main menu. You can work with your caterer on this point. Also include menu items for kids if kids will attend the event.\n\nMake sure there are easily accessed garbage areas so guests can dispose of any garbage without causingany unsightly buildup.\n<h1><b>Offsite Events</b></h1>\nSometimes its good to take employees, customers and partners to an offsite location for a picnic or to agreat location like a hotel, local restaurant or conference center. Choose a location that is large enoughfor everyone that could be in attendance. The event host should have answers to how many people theroom can hold, who can provide the catering and who can provide food and drink service. Check withhost and caterer to see what is all included as part of the event package including glasses, seating, tablelinens, dinnerware, etc.\n\nMany restaurants offer party menus if you book in advance. These are often delicious sampling of all thefood on their menu and are a great way to satisfy many people at once. As with on-site planning, workwith the host or caterer to create a menu that satisfies all in attendance. Include a few surprise items onboth the food and drink menu. This will get guests talking about the event making even more of a hit.\n\nLet your caterer do what they do best! They are experts in delicious food and drinks so let them guideyou through the process. It will lead to a great event that celebrates your employees, customers andpartners!\n<h6 class=\"zemanta-related-title\" style=\"font-size: 1em\">Related articles</h6>\n<ul class=\"zemanta-article-ul zemanta-article-ul-image\" style=\"margin: 0;padding: 0;overflow: hidden\">\n	<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li-image zemanta-article-ul-li\" style=\"padding: 0;background: none;float: left;vertical-align: top;text-align: left;width: 84px;font-size: 11px;margin: 2px 10px 10px 2px\"><a style=\"padding: 2px;text-decoration: none\" href=\"http://peranyc.com/blog/how-to-plan-a-successful-in-office-business-lunch-meeting/\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"padding: 0;margin: 0;border: 0;width: 80px\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://i.zemanta.com/156666973_80_80.jpg\" /></a><a style=\"overflow: hidden;text-decoration: none;line-height: 12pt;height: 80px;padding: 5px 2px 0 2px\" href=\"http://peranyc.com/blog/how-to-plan-a-successful-in-office-business-lunch-meeting/\" target=\"_blank\">How to Plan A Successful In-Office Business Lunch Meeting</a></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/?px\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none;float: right\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=4c8a5f30-7235-4d0d-a957-0695be08f6e8\" /></a></div>", "Business Celebration: How to Plan for the Perfect Catered Business Event", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "business-celebration-how-to-plan-for-the-perfect-catered-business-event", "", "", "2013-05-10 16:02:23", "2013-05-10 16:02:23", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=164", "0", "post", "", "0");
