INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("362", "2", "2013-05-22 18:11:18", "2013-05-22 18:11:18", "<p style=\"text-align: justify\">If youre in the mood for intricately spiced meats and vegetables, healthy carbs, delicate fish dishes, and naturally sweet desserts, youre looking for modern Turkish cuisine! Its exciting to see the many Mediterranean and Turkish restaurants out there. Many of them are using pared down language, fusion dishes, and local ingredients to entice new customers and those familiar with traditional Turkish fare to come in and sample their menus.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><a href=\"http://pera.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/pic-09.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-380 alignleft\" alt=\"Adana\" src=\"http://pera.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/pic-09-300x199.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>Holding true to traditional Turkish cuisine, modern chefs in the United States use the popular ingredients of lamb, chicken, fish, beef, eggplant, onions, garlic, tomatoes, and lentils in their dishes. Breakfast dishes and desserts dishes alike tend to include yoghurt, honey, nuts, and dried fruits that are common in traditional Turkish cuisine but often have new twists to make them unique and appealing. Adding berry compote to a Greek yoghurt parfait could change it from traditional to exciting. Using techniques like smoking and creating fusions between cultures has kept Turkish food current and interesting to todays ever-changing palates.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\"><a href=\"http://pera.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/pic-10.jpg\"><img class=\"size-medium wp-image-382 alignright\" alt=\"pic-10\" src=\"http://pera.wpengine.com/wp-content/uploads/2013/05/pic-10-300x199.jpg\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a>One way American chefs and restaurant managers alike are making Turkish food more accessible is foregoing traditional names and making the dishes enticing by using descriptions of simple, fresh ingredients. While some people may know what dolma are, referring to them as stuffed grape leaves on the menus tells patrons exactly what theyre ordering- without having to pull out their smart phones to look it up. Using traditional Turkish names but also describing what is in the dish - Fresh Lamb Adana for example- describes what is included in the ingredients list while letting guests learn the Turkish name for things. They are sure to remember it if they loved it and can look for it on the menu again!</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Fruit in many regions of Turkey is rich and abundant. Fresh fruits would often accompany meat dishes in traditional cuisine. Dried fruits are still used in pilafs and desserts in modern cuisine. Experimenting with fruits and creating sauces and compotes out of interesting and unusual combinations, like fig and pomegranate, keeps menus fresh. Incorporating fresh fruits is one way chefs are keeping Turkish cuisine healthy while adding sweetness and unexpected flavors to dishes.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">One of the most popular parts of traditional Turkish cuisine that has tracked through to modern dishes is the use of seasonal fruits and vegetables to make menus special. With a focus on the environment and carbon footprints so prevalent in society today, establishments that use local and regional produce has become something many patrons look for in their favorite and frequented restaurants.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Even if youre familiar with all the traditional foods that are available in Turkey, you can find something new, interesting, and fresh in the US. Look for the authentic flavors and spices of traditional foods that are paired with new wine selections, creative side dishes, or local favorites. You will still find traditional dishes like<a class=\"zem_slink\" title=\"Karnyark\" href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Karn%C4%B1yar%C4%B1k\" target=\"_blank\" rel=\"wikipedia\">Karnyark</a>, Yaprak Sarma, Kfte, and Kebabsthey may just be called something you arent expecting.</p>\n\n<h6 class=\"zemanta-related-title\" style=\"font-size: 1em;text-align: justify\">Related articles</h6>\n<ul class=\"zemanta-article-ul zemanta-article-ul-image\" style=\"margin: 0px;padding: 0px;overflow: hidden;text-align: justify\">\n	<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li-image zemanta-article-ul-li\" style=\"padding: 0;background: none;float: left;vertical-align: top;text-align: left;width: 84px;font-size: 11px;margin: 2px 10px 10px 2px\"><a style=\"padding: 2px;text-decoration: none\" href=\"http://peranyc.com/blog/turkish-delight-traditional-food-and-wine-of-turkey/\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"padding: 0;margin: 0;border: 0;width: 80px\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://i.zemanta.com/169465156_80_80.jpg\" /></a><a style=\"overflow: hidden;text-decoration: none;line-height: 12pt;height: 80px;padding: 5px 2px 0 2px\" href=\"http://peranyc.com/blog/turkish-delight-traditional-food-and-wine-of-turkey/\" target=\"_blank\">Turkish Delight: Traditional Food and Wine of Turkey</a></li>\n	<li class=\"zemanta-article-ul-li-image zemanta-article-ul-li\" style=\"padding: 0;background: none;float: left;vertical-align: top;text-align: left;width: 84px;font-size: 11px;margin: 2px 10px 10px 2px\"><a style=\"padding: 2px;text-decoration: none\" href=\"http://peranyc.com/blog/a-guide-to-traveling-in-turkey/\" target=\"_blank\"><img style=\"padding: 0;margin: 0;border: 0;width: 80px\" alt=\"\" src=\"http://i.zemanta.com/168221143_80_80.jpg\" /></a><a style=\"overflow: hidden;text-decoration: none;line-height: 12pt;height: 80px;padding: 5px 2px 0 2px\" href=\"http://peranyc.com/blog/a-guide-to-traveling-in-turkey/\" target=\"_blank\">A Guide to Traveling in Turkey</a></li>\n</ul>\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px;text-align: justify\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/?px\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none;float: right\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=c1d77db2-c336-4796-b647-56c38842aa81\" /></a></div>", "A Complete Guide to Modern Turkish Cuisine", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "a-complete-guide-to-modern-turkish-cuisine", "", "", "2013-05-22 18:11:18", "2013-05-22 18:11:18", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=362", "0", "post", "", "0");
