INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("884", "2", "2013-07-04 14:12:00", "2013-07-04 14:12:00", "Every country has their own unique experiences, be it customs, traditions, or places to visit.To truly enjoy Turkey, dont miss some of the most unique Turkish experiences listed below!\n\n&nbsp;\n<h2>1. Hamam (Turkish Bath)</h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"150\"]<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Turkish_bath_%28hamam%29.JPG\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Turkish bath (hamam) in Instanbul (Turkey)\" alt=\"Turkish bath (hamam) in Instanbul (Turkey)\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/eb/Turkish_bath_%28hamam%29.JPG/300px-Turkish_bath_%28hamam%29.JPG\" width=\"150\" /></a> Turkish bath (hamam) in Istanbul[/caption]\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If you find yourself in Turkey, one thing you must do is visit a Hamam, or Turkish bath. Consider doing this after youve spent a few days exploring Turkey and hiking in the gorgeous mountains. You will want the rest and relaxation a Turkish bath can offer.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You start off in a warm room where you are meant to relax and perspire. Moving on to a hot room, similar to a sauna, you spend a little more time relaxing and sweating. After a cold-water splash, and depending on the bath options youve chosen, you will be taken somewhere to be washed, scrubbed, massaged, and cleansed. After rinsing, you will be taken to a cooling room where you complete your relaxing experience at a Turkish bath.</p>\n\n<h2>2. Pamukkale Thermal Pools</h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"150\"]<a href=\"http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Pamukkale_001.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"The pools of Pamukkale\" alt=\"The pools of Pamukkale\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/7/77/Pamukkale_001.jpg/300px-Pamukkale_001.jpg\" width=\"150\" /></a> The pools of Pamukkale[/caption]\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The World Heritage recognizes the Hieroplois ruins, which are adjacent to the city of Pamukkale. Natural thermal pools are what have created travertine formations found throughout the area. Not only are the thermal pools a great way to spend an afternoon, but also there are ruins and museums all around to explore. The Roman Bath has been used as the Archeology Museum since 1984 and is one of the best places to see examples of crafts from the Bronze Age.</p>\n\n<h2>3. Whirling Dervishes</h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"150\"]<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Mevlevi_dervishes_1887.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Mevlevi dervishes. 1887.\" alt=\"Mevlevi dervishes. 1887.\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/4c/Mevlevi_dervishes_1887.jpg/300px-Mevlevi_dervishes_1887.jpg\" width=\"150\" /></a> Mevlevi dervishes. 1887[/caption]\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Watching this deeply entrancing religious experience can be profound in itself. Though not intended as a form of entertainment, watching the practice has become a tourist attraction in Turkey. Seeing the colors of the dervishs robes spinning are enough to draw a crowd. The Mevlevi Order performs this act primarily as part of the Sema Ceremony. There are many places in Istanbul to witness the ceremony with performances daily in some areas.</p>\n\n<h2>4. Ruins of Troy</h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"150\"]<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Ruins_of_Troy.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Ruins of Troy\" alt=\"Ruins of Troy\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/9/9d/Ruins_of_Troy.jpg/300px-Ruins_of_Troy.jpg\" width=\"150\" /></a> Ruins of Troy[/caption]\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Long before it was even Turkey, the City of Troy stood as both an actual city and one of fictional importance. Helens birthplace, made famous for Homers Iliad, and rich with history, this isnt a site to miss. The Roman city of Ilium was built over the site and flourished until Constantinople. The site is rich with history and culture. If youre anything of a history buff, you definitely want to check out the ruins of the city of Troy.</p>\n\n<h2>5. Republic Day at Kas</h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Seeing a celebration with a parade much like other Independence Day parades is an excellent reminder of the history behind other countrys establishment in the world. The little town of Kas offers unparalleled views of the Mediterranean Sea and if youre lucky enough to be nearby on Turkeys National Holiday, Republic Day, youll surely be in for a treat with the parade and special food served.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">With so many things to do in Turkey, you may not reach everything on this list. Consider the most important things about your trip for yourself, whether it is the history, the culture, the food, or the seas you will surely have your own unique Turkish experience, just so long as you step outside your hotel room!</p>\n&nbsp;\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/?px\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none;float: right\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=e031929e-f0ac-4535-9633-12ef993b84d4\" /></a></div>", "5 Unique Turkish Experiences", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "5-unique-turkish-experiences", "", "", "2013-07-04 14:12:00", "2013-07-04 14:12:00", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=884", "0", "post", "", "0");
