INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("1002", "2", "2013-07-24 13:51:30", "2013-07-24 13:51:30", "<p dir=\"ltr\">The hustle and bustle of the big city can be exhilarating on a summers day.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">It can also be exhausting.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Take a weekend and enjoy one of the millions of places you can go by train, bus, or car right from your own front door.Whether you want to visit the beach, the mountains, or a place outside of the ordinary, you can find it just a short trip away.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Check out the ideas below of 5 places to visit near NYC.</p>\n\n<h2>Lewes, Delaware: History and the Beach</h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"240\"]<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/78418066@N00/3007075795\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Lewes\" alt=\"Lewes\" src=\"http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3296/3007075795_a332e4c12e_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"180\" /></a> Lewes (Photo credit: Mark Bridge)[/caption]\n<p dir=\"ltr\">If youre any sort of history buff youll love to spend one of your summer weekends in Lewes, Delaware. Billed as the first town in the first state, this historic town has buildings dating back to the 1600s for you to explore.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The historic district boasts bed and breakfasts where you can spend the weekend, and enjoy the many shops and restaurants the area has to offer. The beach offers many water sports including surfing and jet skiing so make sure to pack your swimsuit!</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The Cape May-Lewes Ferry is a fun way to hop from New Jersey to this little Delaware town.</p>\n\n<h2>Lititz, Pennsylvania: Small Town Charm with a Modern Twist</h2>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">A 4-hour train ride from NYC will take you to Lancaster, PA.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Just 6 miles north of the train station youll find Americas Coolest Small Town of 2013. Voted by the public, Lititz won this honor for its unique contrast of traditional Amish values against the modern technology that comes with producing some of the worlds largest concert tours. Thats right. Everyone from Lady Gaga to Bon Jovi has spent time in this small town.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You can stay at the General Sutter Inn right in the heart of Lititz. The suites at the General Sutter were recently renovated and deemed the Rock Lititz Suites and you can truly feel like a rock star while also being immersed in Pennsylvania Dutch culture.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">You wont forget this unique experience.</p>\n\n<h2>Lake Placid, New York: Sports History and Mountain Air</h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"300\"]<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:LakePlacid.JPG\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"English: Lake Placid from Whiteface mountain top\" alt=\"English: Lake Placid from Whiteface mountain top\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/e/ec/LakePlacid.JPG/300px-LakePlacid.JPG\" width=\"300\" height=\"199\" /></a> Lake Placid from Whiteface mountain top (Photo credit: Wikipedia)[/caption]\n<p dir=\"ltr\">While this is a great destination in the Adirondack Mountains for winter sports buffs, this beautiful town offers mountaintop views and a shoreline to love for a summer weekend.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The 1980 Winter Olympics were held in Lake Placid and the Lake Placid Olympic Center is a great place to start the tour. There is an Olympic Site Passport you can purchase to save on all the opportunities for tours of the facility.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">The Lake Placid Lake shores are also a popular place to relax.</p>\n\n<h2>Easton, Connecticut: Apple Picking and Lighthouse Park</h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignleft\" width=\"240\"]<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/7327243@N05/4598423394\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Easton, Connecticut\" alt=\"Easton, Connecticut\" src=\"http://farm5.static.flickr.com/4068/4598423394_ec1d9fa786_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"180\" /></a> Easton, Connecticut (Photo credit: Dougtone)[/caption]\n<p dir=\"ltr\">For a fun weekend adventure with the little ones, head to Silvermans Farm in Easton, Connecticut for apple picking.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Check out the petting zoo, shop at the farm market where you can purchase pies and canned goods, and be sure to look for their seasonal activities- you may just be able to get your face painted and see an awesome live band!</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">This is also about a 45-minute drive from Lighthouse Park, which is a must-see on any Connecticut adventure.</p>\n\n<h2>Bethel, New York: Woodstock History and a New Festival</h2>\n[caption id=\"\" align=\"alignright\" width=\"240\"]<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/55999734@N00/7861114162\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Bethel woods museum,Bethel ,NY\" alt=\"Bethel woods museum,Bethel ,NY\" src=\"http://farm9.static.flickr.com/8306/7861114162_24f87afc80_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"160\" /></a> Bethel woods museum,Bethel ,NY[/caption]\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Embrace your inner hippie and head to the birthplace of Woodstock.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">Bethel, NY has preserved the dairy farms and fields the festival was originally held in and now boasts a popular music festival in the summer months at the outdoor pavilion. You may just be able to find one of your favorite bands playing here and a weekend out of the city is the perfect way to treat yourself after a long week at work.</p>\n<p dir=\"ltr\">There are more advantages to living in the city than great shopping and amazing restaurants. Being in a central location to millions of getaway opportunities is definitely something anyone living in NYC should take full advantage of while the summer still lasts! Dont forget the sunscreen!</p>\n\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/?px\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none;float: right\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=f421058a-6226-41b0-9b60-e894ebb96891\" /></a></div>", "5 Late Summer Weekend Getaways Near NYC", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "5-places-to-visit-near-nyc-for-late-summer-weekend-getaways", "", "", "2013-07-24 13:51:30", "2013-07-24 13:51:30", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=1002", "0", "post", "", "0");
