INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("1173", "2", "2013-10-29 17:38:37", "2013-10-29 17:38:37", "<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Midtown Manhattans Bryant Park, located behind the New York Public Library, is popular with both locals and tourists alike. The park was originally known as Reservoir Square and was situated next to the Croton Distributing Reservoir. In 1853, it was the site of the Crystal Palace Exhibition, and it was renamed Bryant Park in 1884. From 1922 to 1927, the park became a dumping ground for debris from the construction of the Interborough Rapid Transit subway tunnel, but it was redesigned and reopened to the public in 1934; however, by the late 1970s, the park had once again fallen into disrepair. During the 1980s, the Bryant Park Restoration Corporation put forth a successful effort to reduce crime and bring visitors back to the park, resulting in the parks reopening in 1992. Today, Bryant Park is frequented by thousands of people daily and offers a variety of activities that can be enjoyed throughout the year.</p>\n<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Bryant_Park_NY.JPG\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"A photo of Bryant Park, Manhattan NY.\" alt=\"A photo of Bryant Park, Manhattan NY.\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/f/fd/Bryant_Park_NY.JPG/300px-Bryant_Park_NY.JPG\" width=\"150\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Strolling the grounds of Bryant Park is a favorite pursuit; the park features gardens, promenades and an expansive lawn, allowing visitors to enjoy the beauty of nature year-round. The gardens are located on the northern and southern boundaries of the lawn and are filled with seasonal plants and flowers. Tree-lined promenades border the park on its north and south sides and are designed to enhance the parks European style. During the warmer months, the green, grassy oasis of the lawn is often filled with picnickers enjoying a respite from the concrete and asphalt of bustling Manhattan.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">For those visitors seeking cultural enrichment, the Bryant Park Reading Room is the perfect destination. The Reading Room was started during the Great Depression so that unemployed individuals had somewhere to pursue intellectual activities and was revived by the Bryant Park Restoration Corporation in the 1980s. Books and periodicals can be borrowed for free and enjoyed in the beautiful surroundings of the park. The Reading Room also hosts free programs such as Word for Word Poetry and story time for children.</p>\n<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/83286413@N00/5704899863\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Bryant Park | New York City\" alt=\"Bryant Park | New York City\" src=\"http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3266/5704899863_057296dbcb_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"159\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Bryant Park also offers a multitude of games for visitors enjoyment. The Marshall Chess Club provides monitors for chess games and can arrange games for those without a ready opponent. At the 40th Street Plaza, visitors can participate in Scrabble, dominoes, Jenga and other table games. The southwest corner of the park along 6th Avenue features a putting green with five holes, and equipment is provided free of charge. There are also two ping-pong tables near 42nd Street and 6th Avenue; time slots can be reserved with a park attendant.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">The gastronomically inclined will have no problem satiating their appetite at one of Bryant Parks dining establishments. The Bryant Park Grille, located behind the library on the Upper Terrace, serves modern American cuisine with beautiful park views from the patio and rooftop garden. Next door, the Bryant Park Caf offers casual, open-air dining and is especially popular with locals after work during the summer. And of course, Pera Mediterranean Brasserie offers elegant and sophisticated dining year round just a block away.</p>\n<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/11967895@N05/3054982688\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Bryant Park\" alt=\"Bryant Park\" src=\"http://farm4.static.flickr.com/3238/3054982688_066ef94053_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"179\" /></a>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Although not a year round activity, between November and March,Bryant Park is transformed into the annual Holiday Market. The Holiday Shops at Bryant Park are a favorite for both locals and tourists alike, with over 100 seasonal kiosks and stands selling everything from hand-crafted holiday decor to artisan jewelry. And let\'s not forget the free ice skating rink, the centerpiece of the Bryant Park Winter Village.</p>\n<p style=\"text-align: justify\">Whether walking through the beautiful grounds, lounging on the lawn, thumbing through a book or magazine, battling an opponent in chess or enjoying a delicious meal, visitors will find no end to the opportunities for relaxation and entertainment. Whatever the season, Bryant Park has something for everyone.</p>\n\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/?px\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none;float: right\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=bf71850a-894d-4c7a-a20c-7d3b846e5f80\" /></a></div>", "Year-Round Activities In Bryant Park", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "year-round-activities-in-bryant-park", "", "", "2013-10-29 17:38:37", "2013-10-29 17:38:37", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=1173", "0", "post", "", "0");
