INSERT INTO `wp_posts` VALUES("1219", "2", "2013-11-14 19:19:49", "2013-11-14 19:19:49", "Turkish cuisine specializes in freshly grown fruits which are native to the country. The amount of fruit production in Turkey is plentiful due to the rich soil, nutrients, and land available for cultivation. Fruit production is one of the main facets of farming and commerce that drives Turkeys diverse economy.\n\nThe variations in climate are one of the key factors in the successful cultivation of fruits in Turkey. Among the most popular fruits, the Turkish culture has embraced several fruits that are eaten around the world.\n<h2>APPLE</h2>\n<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/30928442@N08/5496562168\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Apple Man\" alt=\"Apple Man\" src=\"http://farm6.static.flickr.com/5300/5496562168_97e3d57c8f_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"240\" /></a>\n\nOne of the most successful crops in Turkey in terms of fruit is the apple. Turkey is where apples became domesticated and used as a routine fruit in the diet. There are a variety of apple types that are native to the country. Among the well-known varieties in Turkey include the Amasya and Ferik. While these particular types of apples are popular among the Turkish population, better known varieties such as the Golden Delicious and Red Delicious are imported to Turkey where they are also produced. The apple is typically used for desserts and sweet dishes.\n<h2>APRICOT</h2>\n<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/53470512@N07/6822008239\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Organic Turkish Apricots\" alt=\"Organic Turkish Apricots\" src=\"http://farm8.static.flickr.com/7030/6822008239_e44368f31f_m.jpg\" width=\"240\" height=\"240\" /></a>\n\nA popular fruit of Turkey that is produced for a variety of cuisine options is the apricot. The worlds largest supplier of apricots is Turkey. Cultivated in the Malatya region of Turkey, the apricot can be used in Turkish cuisine fresh, cooked, or dried. In Turkey, apricots are used in baking and for snacking.\n<h2>CHERRIES</h2>\n<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Bing_Cherries_%28USDA_ARS%29.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"The Bing cherry owes its development to the Ch...\" alt=\"The Bing cherry owes its development to the Ch...\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/40/Bing_Cherries_%28USDA_ARS%29.jpg/300px-Bing_Cherries_%28USDA_ARS%29.jpg\" width=\"120\" /></a>\n\nCherries are another standard fruit grown in Turkey. The cherry, (like the apple), derives from the rose family of fruits. In Turkey, there are two main types of cherries. The sweet cherry consists of darker skin and flesh, and has a pleasant sweetness. The sweet cherry is cultivated mainly in the Afyon region of the country where conditions are perfect for cherry production. The sour cherry variety is also grown in the Afyon region. Cherries are found in many baked goods commonly found in Turkey.\n<h2>WATERMELON</h2>\n<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Taiwan_2009_Tainan_City_Organic_Farm_Watermelon_FRD_7962.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"English: Watermelon in a small-scale organic f...\" alt=\"English: Watermelon in a small-scale organic f...\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/4/47/Taiwan_2009_Tainan_City_Organic_Farm_Watermelon_FRD_7962.jpg/300px-Taiwan_2009_Tainan_City_Organic_Farm_Watermelon_FRD_7962.jpg\" width=\"150\" /></a>\n\nTurkey is known for another fruit that shares popularity around the world. The watermelon is grown all around, but especially in the south and southeastern regions of the country. Along with the cantaloupe, the watermelon is exported from Turkey to other countries. The melons from Turkey have some of the sweetest flavors and the flesh of the fruits is firm but soft.\n<h2>RASPBERRY</h2>\n<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Raspberries05.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"English: Raspberries Franais : Framboises Deu...\" alt=\"English: Raspberries Franais : Framboises Deu...\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/6/69/Raspberries05.jpg/300px-Raspberries05.jpg\" width=\"150\" /></a>\n\nThe raspberry is an additional fruit that is cultivated in the mountains of Turkey. Raspberries are hardy growers and it is common to find them growing in home gardens as well. In Turkish cuisine, the raspberry is used in several dishes that require a tangy yet sweet flavor.\n<h2>FIGS</h2>\n<a href=\"http://www.flickr.com/photos/50835495@N00/49115723\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Figs for lunch 4\" alt=\"Figs for lunch 4\" src=\"http://farm1.static.flickr.com/31/49115723_5f58f1886e_m.jpg\" width=\"100\" /></a>\n\nFigs are yet another savory fruit that is native to Turkey. The fig has a multitude of uses in cooking and Turkish recipes utilize them often. Figs are also a favorite snack when eaten dried. There are several regions where fig cultivation is favored including the fertile areas around Istanbul.\n<h2>GRAPES</h2>\n<a href=\"http://commons.wikipedia.org/wiki/File:Grape_00005.jpg\" target=\"_blank\"><img class=\"zemanta-img-inserted zemanta-img-configured\" title=\"Red Grape\" alt=\"Red Grape\" src=\"http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/5/55/Grape_00005.jpg/300px-Grape_00005.jpg\" width=\"150\" /></a>\n\nAmong the many popular fruits of Turkey, grapes are produced and used in Turkey and around the world. Varieties of the grape that are found in Turkey include those that are red, green, yellow, and purple. The darker the color of the grape, the sweeter the variety. Grapes are cultivated in the areas surrounding the Eastern Anatolia region and the Aegean region.\n<div class=\"zemanta-pixie\" style=\"margin-top: 10px;height: 15px\"><a class=\"zemanta-pixie-a\" title=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" href=\"http://www.zemanta.com/?px\"><img class=\"zemanta-pixie-img\" style=\"border: none;float: right\" alt=\"Enhanced by Zemanta\" src=\"http://img.zemanta.com/zemified_e.png?x-id=c16ed4cd-3625-4e2f-9b77-38421a5124f4\" /></a></div>", "Popular Fruits of Turkey", "", "publish", "closed", "closed", "", "popular-fruits-of-turkey", "", "", "2013-11-14 19:19:49", "2013-11-14 19:19:49", "", "0", "http://peranyc.com/blog/?p=1219", "0", "post", "", "0");
